WEBVTT

00:01.160 --> 00:04.160
ARTHUR: This place is
under new management.

00:05.040 --> 00:07.440
<i>By order of the Peaky Blinders.</i>

00:07.720 --> 00:09.280
Just write down "peace", right,

00:09.640 --> 00:13.960
between the Jews and the Italians.

00:14.280 --> 00:17.720
And war against the gypsies.

00:18.640 --> 00:19.680
(CHEERING)

00:19.760 --> 00:21.320
POLLY: <i>I love him, Tom.</i>
TOMMY: <i>I know.</i>

00:21.760 --> 00:24.560
That's why I'll keep him away
from the old business,

00:24.640 --> 00:26.160
put him charge of the new.

00:26.280 --> 00:27.920
MICHAEL: <i>Some idiots
at the Marquis of Lorne.</i>

00:28.280 --> 00:30.640
Tried to stop me and Isaiah
from drinking, but it's all right.

00:30.760 --> 00:32.000
We fought them off.

00:32.320 --> 00:33.720
The Marquis, eh?

00:38.840 --> 00:40.240
What do we want with
a 1,000-guinea horse?

00:40.440 --> 00:42.760
When we make our move
on Sabini's racing pitches,

00:42.840 --> 00:45.440
<i>a good race horse is a passport
to the owner's enclosure.</i>

00:45.640 --> 00:48.040
May Car let on.
I breed racehorses and train them.

00:54.280 --> 00:57.520
TOMMY: <i>I've made arrangements
with men I trust.</i>

00:58.000 --> 01:01.560
If I should die, then you will die.

01:06.840 --> 01:07.840
(GOAT BLEATING)

01:19.200 --> 01:20.640
(CROWD MURMURING)

01:28.880 --> 01:29.880
Thanks.

01:36.760 --> 01:38.200
(WOMAN MOANING)

01:43.840 --> 01:45.080
Would you stop the noise?

01:47.440 --> 01:48.800
(GRUNTING)

01:52.640 --> 01:53.640
(GOAT BLEATING)

02:10.440 --> 02:12.000
You working tonight?

02:12.080 --> 02:13.280
(SCOFFS)

02:13.440 --> 02:15.400
Not so much work as pleasure.

02:16.160 --> 02:18.640
Others are doing my work
for me tonight.

02:19.920 --> 02:20.920
Gentlemen, welcome!

02:21.000 --> 02:22.160
Welcome!

02:22.240 --> 02:23.400
Mr Solomon.

02:23.520 --> 02:24.920
You must be Arthur.

02:25.080 --> 02:26.560
-That is right.
-Arthur!

02:27.160 --> 02:29.080
-Arthur!
-Pleasure to meet you, sir.

02:29.160 --> 02:30.840
I've heard so much about you.

02:31.320 --> 02:33.840
Shalom. Let me just say.

02:34.720 --> 02:36.000
Shalom.

02:38.600 --> 02:39.600
(DISH BREAKING)

02:40.320 --> 02:41.440
For luck.

02:42.920 --> 02:44.080
(GUNS LOADING)

03:00.120 --> 03:02.800
You understand I'm the commanding
officer on this operation.

03:03.240 --> 03:05.040
You're here purely as an observer.

03:07.600 --> 03:09.040
Just do your duty.

03:11.280 --> 03:12.320
POLLY: Dear Lord,

03:13.320 --> 03:17.320
for what we're about to receive
may the Lord make us truly grateful.

03:17.600 --> 03:18.800
Amen.

03:23.000 --> 03:24.080
Amen.

03:25.680 --> 03:26.680
Amen.

03:29.520 --> 03:33.240
Passover started off
way out there in the Far East,

03:33.320 --> 03:36.800
out in the sand, out in the desert,
where me forefathers come from.

03:37.040 --> 03:39.160
You know, the Jews, the brews,
whatever you want to call them.

03:39.240 --> 03:40.640
(HEAVY METAL DOOR CLOSING)

03:40.720 --> 03:42.400
It started out
as a little speck on the horizon.

03:42.520 --> 03:43.520
Arthur, this ain't right.

03:43.600 --> 03:46.280
Billy, don't worry, mate, you know
what I mean? If you want, you can leave.

03:46.560 --> 03:48.960
If you need to go
to the little boys' room, you can leave.

03:49.040 --> 03:50.120
We going to open 'em in a minute.

03:50.240 --> 03:52.320
He's all right, he's all right,
Billy boy.

03:52.400 --> 03:53.440
-Do you want to leave?
-No, you're all right.

03:53.680 --> 03:55.480
-You want to stay?
-I'll stay.

03:56.000 --> 03:57.520
You stay there, then, treacle.

03:57.760 --> 04:01.520
Okay, so the pharaoh.
Have you heard of him?

04:01.640 --> 04:05.480
He kept my people,
the Jewish people, in slavery,

04:05.560 --> 04:08.000
for thousands and thousands of years.

04:08.080 --> 04:09.480
Persecuted race.

04:09.800 --> 04:12.720
He did, he persecuted my race.

04:12.960 --> 04:14.960
The killing of the innocent, right?

04:15.280 --> 04:18.200
<i>Seder, this feast,
that what we is having here.</i>

04:18.520 --> 04:23.640
<i>Seder is basically the day what
when the Jewish angels decided,</i>

04:23.720 --> 04:26.800
<i>you know, that the evil
fucking Egyptians</i>

04:26.880 --> 04:28.680
<i>had pushed their fucking luck!</i>

04:28.760 --> 04:29.920
ARTHUR: <i>Right.</i>

04:30.000 --> 04:33.440
ALFIE: <i>lt is part of our tradition
to do with Seder, right,</i>

04:33.560 --> 04:38.320
<i>that in order to make it good
with God to kill a king,</i>

04:40.000 --> 04:43.480
<i>we have to carry out the Korban Pesach.</i>

04:43.800 --> 04:45.280
-Right.
-That,

04:45.600 --> 04:49.720
is the ritual sacrifice
of the Passover goat.

04:50.920 --> 04:52.400
(GOAT BLEATING)

04:54.680 --> 04:58.160
-It's a goat.
-Yeah, and we're gonna sacrifice it.

04:59.280 --> 05:04.400
<i>Tonight. That's part of the reason
why we have to shut the doors as well.</i>

05:04.960 --> 05:08.440
But this year we thought
we'd give the fucking goat a name.

05:08.720 --> 05:11.520
-You've named it?
-We fucking did, yeah.

05:11.840 --> 05:15.960
-They named the fucking goat.
-The evil fucking Egyptian pharaoh,

05:16.160 --> 05:17.680
-the fucking enemy.
-That's right.

05:17.760 --> 05:19.600
-You know what we called it?
-What did ya call him?

05:19.680 --> 05:20.720
Tommy Shelby.

05:21.760 --> 05:23.040
-(GUN FIRING)
-(SHOUTING)

05:28.440 --> 05:29.440
(STRUGGLING)

05:37.400 --> 05:38.560
(DOORS OPENING)

05:38.640 --> 05:41.440
-Stay where you are!
-(INDISTINCT SHOUTING)

05:44.800 --> 05:45.960
You're all fired.

05:46.160 --> 05:48.120
-Fuck you.
-(GRUNTING)

05:48.880 --> 05:51.720
-That's right, let's take a load off.
-(GASPING)

05:53.200 --> 05:54.240
So...

05:55.520 --> 05:57.600
And the evil Egyptian scum...

05:57.680 --> 05:58.840
(BREATHING HEAVILY)

05:58.920 --> 06:00.800
...was finally cleansed,

06:01.120 --> 06:04.120
with the blood
of the Passover goat, mate.

06:05.080 --> 06:06.080
(GASPING)

06:11.920 --> 06:13.480
That's from Sabini.

06:14.880 --> 06:16.720
And tell your gypsy king...

06:17.160 --> 06:18.160
(SCREAMING)

06:18.240 --> 06:21.720
...whoever comes
down south, shall return north

06:22.280 --> 06:25.640
in many fucking pieces. Huh?

06:28.320 --> 06:29.560
(SCREAMING)

06:38.440 --> 06:39.480
(DOOR UNLOCKING)

06:39.560 --> 06:42.960
This fucking animal. He come in here,
right, with a fucking gun and razor

06:43.040 --> 06:44.960
and he shot him in the face!

06:45.040 --> 06:47.000
And my lads, they restrained him.

06:47.280 --> 06:49.240
Look at him. He's dead. Is he dead?

06:49.800 --> 06:51.200
He's fucking dead!

06:51.560 --> 06:53.520
He wants arresting or something, right?

06:53.680 --> 06:55.280
Surely.

07:01.840 --> 07:05.840
Michael! You can't take him away again,
you can't take my son away!

07:06.240 --> 07:09.360
You come back here! No! No!

07:09.680 --> 07:10.680
(SHOUTING)

07:11.280 --> 07:12.440
Ow!

07:12.640 --> 07:15.560
Don't you fucking touch him!
Get off him!

07:16.000 --> 07:18.000
Don't say anything!
Tommy will get you out!

07:18.080 --> 07:19.080
Fuck!

07:19.160 --> 07:21.240
I'll be all right...

07:25.640 --> 07:30.480
You should know, that as of this night,
Tommy Shelby is finished.

07:44.760 --> 07:47.760
Mick? This is Thomas Shelby,
he's come to check up on his filly.

07:49.960 --> 07:51.240
Yes, I've heard about you.

07:52.960 --> 07:54.480
MAY: Mick is
the best horseman in England.

07:56.960 --> 07:59.120
He likes to waste money, I know that.

07:59.360 --> 08:01.000
According to the reports
I've been given,

08:01.080 --> 08:03.200
you're spending two pound a month
on worming powder.

08:03.560 --> 08:05.080
What? You want a horse with worms?

08:05.240 --> 08:07.120
Horses get worms from the water trough.

08:07.720 --> 08:09.840
Put goldfish in them,
they eat the worm eggs.

08:09.920 --> 08:11.000
Goldfish?

08:12.520 --> 08:14.520
-It'll be a gypsy thing, is it?
-No.

08:15.120 --> 08:16.400
It's an accounting thing.

08:17.320 --> 08:20.320
-Goldfish cost a penny each.
-Or you can win them at the fair.

08:24.320 --> 08:27.480
If you want, I'll dispense
with the vet altogether. Excuse me.

08:31.520 --> 08:33.360
Did you ever consider
a career in diplomacy?

08:38.240 --> 08:39.720
Hello, hello.

08:39.800 --> 08:40.880
How are you, eh?

08:41.280 --> 08:42.360
Goldfish, seriously?

08:42.800 --> 08:43.920
Yup.

08:44.480 --> 08:46.160
You people have a lot to learn.

09:04.240 --> 09:07.720
They asked me if I wanted a fire
in the guest bedroom.

09:10.120 --> 09:11.320
I said no.

09:13.880 --> 09:15.040
Just one fire tonight.

09:16.960 --> 09:18.400
Bold and fearless, eh?

09:19.040 --> 09:20.120
Yes.

09:21.800 --> 09:23.320
Though I'm not really fearless.

09:32.920 --> 09:35.240
-Drink?
-Why not?

09:48.920 --> 09:52.280
-Madam, there is a telephone call.
-I'll take it in the drawing room.

09:52.560 --> 09:53.960
It's for Mr Shelby.

09:57.960 --> 09:59.200
TOMMY: We had a deal.

10:00.440 --> 10:01.640
Hey!

10:02.440 --> 10:04.120
We had a fucking deal.

10:04.840 --> 10:08.320
I would thank you to moderate
your language in a place of worship.

10:10.000 --> 10:12.120
We had a fucking deal.

10:15.440 --> 10:16.560
Mr Shelby.

10:18.960 --> 10:20.720
If you read the papers,

10:21.720 --> 10:24.880
you might have seen that
the Home Secretary has got himself

10:24.960 --> 10:28.960
into a bit of a fizz
about certain moral issues.

10:29.440 --> 10:30.640
Prostitution.

10:31.120 --> 10:35.000
Protection, racketeering, drinking,
cocaine and, of course,

10:36.000 --> 10:37.400
gambling.

10:38.200 --> 10:39.720
And he's demanded results.

10:40.120 --> 10:42.560
You offered me protection.

10:42.720 --> 10:44.880
You promised me protection.

10:45.000 --> 10:49.520
Well, no, you see, it was Mr Churchill
that made you that promise.

10:50.800 --> 10:54.280
And the Home Secretary
outranks him, so...

10:56.400 --> 10:58.960
And I can hardly be blamed
if your demented brother

10:59.040 --> 11:02.280
decides to go on some sort
of blood orgy during dinner.

11:02.360 --> 11:03.440
Do not fucking lie to me.

11:03.560 --> 11:07.040
Do not sit here
in your fucking church and lie to me!

11:09.240 --> 11:13.520
You will need to contain your emotions
or this meeting is at an end.

11:22.520 --> 11:23.880
Good.

11:25.480 --> 11:27.000
That's better.

11:29.520 --> 11:30.520
So...

11:32.000 --> 11:35.480
Let us review the new situation.

11:35.800 --> 11:37.720
I have your brother in a prison cell,

11:37.960 --> 11:40.280
charged with the murder
of Billy Kitchen.

11:41.440 --> 11:43.400
The case against him is strong.

11:44.160 --> 11:47.640
And I have no doubt
that his destiny is to hang.

11:48.440 --> 11:50.720
And then there is Polly's son Michael.

11:51.040 --> 11:55.760
He has already admitted to helping
Arthur burn down the Marquis Pub.

11:57.160 --> 12:00.320
Oh, he was
a tough nut to crack, that boy.

12:00.400 --> 12:01.520
But crack he did.

12:02.320 --> 12:04.440
So I have your brother facing the noose.

12:04.520 --> 12:07.080
I have your cousin facing
five years for arson.

12:07.400 --> 12:11.960
And I have
your entire organisation in disarray

12:12.080 --> 12:13.760
in Birmingham and in London.

12:13.840 --> 12:15.000
What do you want?

12:16.400 --> 12:17.680
What do I want?

12:19.040 --> 12:20.280
I don't understand.

12:22.040 --> 12:23.280
I've already agreed

12:23.480 --> 12:25.640
to do your fucking killing for you.

12:26.960 --> 12:30.240
Now what is it you want from me?

12:30.680 --> 12:33.840
Oh. There you go, you see...

12:36.120 --> 12:40.480
An agreement is not the same thing
as an assurance, now, is it?

12:41.960 --> 12:44.280
See, I found that

12:45.240 --> 12:47.080
I wasn't sleeping so well.

12:49.000 --> 12:50.240
And it wasn't just that...

12:50.520 --> 12:53.160
...the smell and the noise
in that room, no.

12:54.160 --> 12:57.440
It was the nagging doubt.
The knowledge.

12:58.240 --> 12:59.760
The knowledge that...

13:01.640 --> 13:04.320
Tommy Shelby is not afraid to die.

13:06.480 --> 13:08.160
And therefore,

13:09.000 --> 13:11.840
the threat to your own life
might not be enough

13:12.440 --> 13:17.080
to make it certain that
you will obey me on the given day.

13:19.280 --> 13:23.720
I needed also the power
of life and death over your family

13:24.000 --> 13:26.440
and that I now have.

13:27.000 --> 13:30.760
Your brother, your cousin
and your sister.

13:32.680 --> 13:37.080
I've known her address in Primrose Hill
since the day she moved in.

13:38.120 --> 13:41.600
Now she is safe only as long
as I want her to be.

13:42.800 --> 13:47.080
I've been ahead of you,
every step of the way.

13:48.600 --> 13:51.600
And, as my father used to say,

13:52.720 --> 13:56.560
to make sure your dog obeys you,
you have to show it the stick

13:57.120 --> 13:58.800
once in a while.

14:03.160 --> 14:04.560
(PHONE RINGING)

14:06.360 --> 14:09.480
Tommy, Arthur's in solitary confinement.
Michael's in remand wing...

14:09.560 --> 14:12.160
Yeah, I already know.
Get out, shut the doors.

14:21.120 --> 14:23.200
(PHONE RINGING)

14:27.160 --> 14:28.240
GRACE: <i>Tommy?</i>

14:30.000 --> 14:31.160
<i>It's me.</i>

14:34.720 --> 14:35.800
Tommy, can you hear me?

14:37.160 --> 14:38.320
Yes, Grace.

14:39.400 --> 14:40.880
I think you called.

14:41.560 --> 14:42.840
I haven't slept.

14:45.640 --> 14:47.480
Grace, this is not a good time.

14:48.200 --> 14:49.400
<i>I can call you back.</i>

14:49.520 --> 14:51.600
-No, no, it's fine. It's all right.
-Can we meet?

14:53.640 --> 14:55.640
Yes, we'll meet.

14:56.520 --> 14:57.640
When?

15:01.400 --> 15:03.600
Grace, there are some things
I have to do first.

15:06.880 --> 15:08.160
(DOOR OPENING)

15:13.200 --> 15:14.440
John?

15:15.560 --> 15:17.960
Coppers have lifted
10 of our men in Camden town,

15:18.840 --> 15:20.200
the rest of them on the run.

15:20.360 --> 15:22.280
-Tom, they've taken Michael.
-Business first.

15:22.360 --> 15:25.320
-They took Michael last night.
-Polly, business first!

15:26.680 --> 15:27.680
John?

15:28.440 --> 15:29.680
They took all our whisky.

15:30.600 --> 15:32.440
So no doubt
they'll be supping that for Christmas.

15:33.560 --> 15:35.440
They've impounded all our vans,

15:35.560 --> 15:37.320
put their own locks on the warehouse.

15:39.120 --> 15:42.680
The Eden Club and all our pubs
have been raided by the coppers

15:43.240 --> 15:45.640
and handed back to Sabini and Solomons.

15:47.920 --> 15:50.240
The Black Country boys think
it was Arthur who killed Billy

15:50.320 --> 15:52.160
because that's what
the coppers told them.

15:52.960 --> 15:55.400
So there'll be no more free passes
for our whisky boats.

15:55.480 --> 15:57.080
I don't give a fuck about whisky.

15:57.160 --> 15:58.960
I don't give a fuck about Billy Kitchen.

15:59.320 --> 16:02.360
I want my son out of prison now.

16:02.440 --> 16:03.800
Thomas, I spoke to Johnny Dogs.

16:03.880 --> 16:05.640
This meeting should just be family.

16:05.720 --> 16:07.640
-I can help.
-It's family only, she's not blood.

16:07.720 --> 16:09.720
-Let her speak.
-Tommy! Or is this a business...

16:09.800 --> 16:10.840
Enough!

16:13.120 --> 16:14.720
Enough, Polly.

16:15.360 --> 16:16.600
Esme.

16:17.000 --> 16:19.120
I spoke to Johnny Dogs.
The Lees are kin.

16:19.200 --> 16:21.360
-The bloody Lees!
-They can give us men.

16:21.440 --> 16:23.240
We don't need more fucking men.

16:23.720 --> 16:26.760
It's men that have done
the damage. It's...

16:27.720 --> 16:31.400
It is men fighting like cockerels that
have put us here in the first place.

16:32.640 --> 16:35.120
Esme, I'll take up their offer.
We need men.

16:42.960 --> 16:46.680
If Michael ever gets out of prison,

16:47.360 --> 16:51.000
I am taking him away
from this family, for good.

16:53.960 --> 16:56.000
This life is bad.

16:59.920 --> 17:02.080
This life is all bad.

17:02.360 --> 17:04.680
-Aunt Pol, what are you doing?
-Shut up and walk.

17:07.480 --> 17:10.320
(DOOR OPENS AND CLOSES)

17:13.720 --> 17:15.080
Thomas.

17:16.880 --> 17:19.200
Should I go and speak
to Queen Mary Lee at the Black Patch?

17:24.360 --> 17:25.640
Yes.

17:26.320 --> 17:28.200
She can give us soldiers
for a few nights.

17:28.360 --> 17:29.560
Mmm, good.

17:33.360 --> 17:36.080
John, go bring up the car.

17:53.720 --> 17:55.560
(DOOR OPENS AND CLOSES)

17:56.760 --> 17:58.480
Imagine riding away, Thomas.

18:00.000 --> 18:01.920
Living the real life, you know?

18:03.280 --> 18:05.080
Your gypsy half is the stronger.

18:07.160 --> 18:08.760
You just want to ride away.

18:11.720 --> 18:13.880
France is the new place
for us, they say.

18:15.440 --> 18:17.400
Lot of metal lying around still.

18:18.120 --> 18:20.480
Guns and trucks
and spent shells and things.

18:22.200 --> 18:23.400
Then you go south.

18:24.880 --> 18:26.000
Saintes Maries.

18:27.160 --> 18:28.600
Where the Black Madonna is.

18:30.200 --> 18:32.080
My brothers go sometimes for the fair.

18:34.440 --> 18:35.840
It's like a home for us.

18:40.080 --> 18:42.200
They still let you get lost there.

18:54.080 --> 18:56.000
I've been to France, Esme.

18:57.960 --> 18:59.360
So has John.

19:01.200 --> 19:04.800
Now get your coat
and go with your husband.

19:15.000 --> 19:18.120
If you ever talk about getting
lost again, I'll cut you

19:19.720 --> 19:21.280
from this family.

19:31.120 --> 19:32.560
What family?

19:48.240 --> 19:49.640
(GATE UNLOCKING)

19:51.560 --> 19:53.200
-(KNOCKING)
-CAMPBELL: Come in.

19:58.440 --> 20:00.840
Ah. Polly.

20:03.000 --> 20:04.640
I've come to see my son.

20:06.120 --> 20:07.520
Close the door.

20:11.560 --> 20:14.920
I've just been conducting
an interrogation.

20:16.360 --> 20:18.200
It can be awfully hard on the hands.

20:19.080 --> 20:21.240
My son. Michael. Where is he?

20:21.960 --> 20:23.600
Do you think I need a shave?

20:26.000 --> 20:27.480
It's been a long day.

20:28.240 --> 20:29.800
I need a shave, don't you think?

20:32.200 --> 20:35.600
Well, maybe it can wait till later.

20:38.200 --> 20:42.040
Your son has been having
a hard time of it I'm told.

20:42.680 --> 20:45.160
And that is why I thought
that you and I together,

20:45.320 --> 20:48.480
we should do whatever we can
to get him freed.

20:49.760 --> 20:52.760
Now, I have a form here, a release form.

20:53.800 --> 20:55.320
With my signature,

20:56.040 --> 20:59.760
he can be freed
by tomorrow morning at dawn.

21:16.120 --> 21:17.320
So sign it.

21:20.560 --> 21:22.640
-He didn't do anything.
-"Sign it,

21:22.840 --> 21:25.720
"Mr Campbell. Please, sir."

21:27.120 --> 21:29.680
Something like that. That would be
a way to say that, wouldn't it?

21:31.920 --> 21:33.080
Now,

21:34.440 --> 21:38.200
what would prompt me
to do you such a favour, hmm?

21:40.880 --> 21:42.280
What do you want?

21:45.240 --> 21:46.320
Information?

21:46.440 --> 21:51.240
You mean inside information about
Tommy Shelby's criminal empire?

21:53.120 --> 21:54.520
With respect,

21:55.320 --> 21:58.200
I would say I know more
about Tommy's dealings than you do.

21:58.640 --> 22:02.120
He doesn't trouble the family with
Irish business for instance, does he?

22:02.360 --> 22:03.400
No.

22:04.360 --> 22:05.680
So, no.

22:07.120 --> 22:09.480
It's not information I need.

22:16.440 --> 22:18.480
What else could you give me

22:20.240 --> 22:22.160
in return for my signature?

22:24.040 --> 22:26.520
I'm talking about
a simple transaction here.

22:28.960 --> 22:30.760
I have a great curiosity.

22:32.640 --> 22:35.480
Like a magpie sees something,

22:37.840 --> 22:39.760
something shining in the mud.

22:41.760 --> 22:44.120
Oh, he has no need for the silver,

22:46.080 --> 22:47.640
but he takes it anyway.

22:59.200 --> 23:00.720
(INHALES SHARPLY)

23:14.440 --> 23:15.800
Sign the form.

23:16.520 --> 23:19.360
-"Please, sir."
-Please, sir.

23:22.920 --> 23:25.960
I will sign that form with this hand

23:27.640 --> 23:29.440
when I am finished.

23:29.880 --> 23:32.800
-It's a deal?
-It's a deal.

23:36.840 --> 23:39.640
-Don't cry.
-Oh, I can cry.

23:40.480 --> 23:41.760
So...

23:43.120 --> 23:44.920
That is what I want.

23:45.360 --> 23:47.320
I need you to cry.

23:49.200 --> 23:50.560
I will try.

23:53.640 --> 23:56.520
"I need a favour, Mr Campbell, sir.

23:56.880 --> 24:00.920
"And I will do anything,
anything in return."

24:01.080 --> 24:03.280
That's what you might have said. Hmm?

24:06.400 --> 24:08.160
I felt something

24:09.960 --> 24:12.000
when I had you up against that car.

24:12.200 --> 24:13.960
And you felt it too.

24:14.440 --> 24:18.320
Don't tell me you didn't,
Polly, because...

24:19.000 --> 24:21.680
Oh, and now you think you're...

24:22.960 --> 24:24.800
You're so respectable,

24:25.240 --> 24:27.840
with your son and your house

24:28.200 --> 24:33.160
and your maid, but I know
what you are, gypsy Fenian slut.

24:34.960 --> 24:37.680
Do you want to do it on the floor
or on the desk, Mr Campbell?

24:42.840 --> 24:44.200
(GRUNTING)

24:47.920 --> 24:49.720
Now you cry.

24:51.080 --> 24:52.640
You cry!

25:00.400 --> 25:02.760
Get out.
Get out.

25:04.760 --> 25:06.080
Get out!

25:06.640 --> 25:09.560
No. No! I want him free.

25:10.880 --> 25:12.400
I'll get him free.

25:16.640 --> 25:18.000
You don't need to shave.

25:20.240 --> 25:21.840
You don't need to do anything.

25:22.480 --> 25:23.840
(BELT UNBUCKLING)

25:24.960 --> 25:27.280
A victory is just doing nothing as well.

25:28.760 --> 25:30.360
Doing it soft and gentle.

25:39.400 --> 25:41.480
Should I talk or not talk?

25:41.760 --> 25:43.320
(GRUNTING)

25:44.560 --> 25:47.440
Should it be like
I'm weak and small, yes?

25:50.920 --> 25:52.840
Do you want me to talk or not to talk?

25:55.600 --> 25:56.720
Talk.

25:57.280 --> 25:58.760
You're small and weak.

25:59.400 --> 26:00.760
(GASPING)

26:00.840 --> 26:01.960
That's what I am...

26:03.360 --> 26:05.040
Small and weak.

26:06.400 --> 26:07.800
Look.

26:13.760 --> 26:15.600
You made me cry.

26:16.720 --> 26:18.880
(GASPING)

26:20.200 --> 26:21.240
No!

26:22.960 --> 26:24.880
We had an agreement, right?

26:25.160 --> 26:26.920
Yes. Yes!

26:31.200 --> 26:32.680
(DOOR OPENING)

26:35.880 --> 26:37.000
Where have you been?

26:39.120 --> 26:41.200
Went to the Spotted Dog in Digbeth.

26:42.200 --> 26:43.440
A glass or two of rum.

26:45.680 --> 26:47.200
Was it one glass or two?

26:47.800 --> 26:49.040
It was three.

26:50.720 --> 26:51.840
Where's the baby?

26:53.280 --> 26:54.560
Sleeping.

26:56.120 --> 26:57.520
More like five.

27:02.720 --> 27:04.520
It was more like six.

27:06.840 --> 27:08.360
Did you meet the maid?

27:09.200 --> 27:11.880
Talked politics with her and
she got bored and went to bed.

27:16.560 --> 27:17.960
I phoned James.

27:18.560 --> 27:20.240
He talked to the lawyer anyway.

27:20.800 --> 27:22.800
Said he'd take Arthur's case for free,

27:23.000 --> 27:24.560
so we don't need Tommy.

27:26.960 --> 27:28.480
(SIGHING)

27:28.560 --> 27:29.560
Pol?

27:30.800 --> 27:33.000
We'll get Michael free
as well, I promise.

27:33.600 --> 27:35.720
There's no need,
they'll let him out in the morning.

27:40.520 --> 27:43.120
If the baby wants anything at night,
ring the bell by the bed.

27:45.520 --> 27:48.440
She gets paid to work 24 hours,
that girl. She's getting lazy.

27:50.440 --> 27:51.800
Well...

27:54.200 --> 27:55.800
Take advantage if you're nice.

28:54.720 --> 28:56.240
(DOOR UNLOCKING)

29:35.600 --> 29:37.720
You need cream on them cuts
or they'll go bad.

29:45.680 --> 29:47.320
The screws told me why I've been freed.

29:52.720 --> 29:54.120
They told me what you did.

30:01.240 --> 30:02.640
They thought it was funny.

30:10.360 --> 30:11.360
Maybe it is.

30:37.120 --> 30:38.840
What are you doing, Tommy?

30:40.080 --> 30:42.160
Shovelling shit, Curly.

30:42.280 --> 30:43.720
Just like you.

30:50.240 --> 30:51.560
Why're you doing that, Tommy?

30:51.640 --> 30:54.680
To remind me self what I'd be

30:54.760 --> 30:56.520
if I wasn't who I am.

31:27.760 --> 31:30.120
Tommy. What's going on?

31:30.200 --> 31:32.840
I think Tommy's lost his mind, Charlie.

31:34.920 --> 31:38.080
Well, it's honest work, Curly.

31:39.400 --> 31:41.440
But I don't want to get used to it.

31:42.520 --> 31:45.000
So I'll need six cans of petrol.

31:45.760 --> 31:47.680
Bring them to the garage.

31:48.360 --> 31:50.440
Put them in the back of the car.

31:50.880 --> 31:52.360
Six cans?

31:53.520 --> 31:54.680
Tommy.

31:55.120 --> 31:57.720
If you ever want a job,
I'll get you your own shovel.

31:59.480 --> 32:02.240
Petrol. Yes. Yeah.

32:53.240 --> 32:55.680
You're far too gorgeous
for some half-blind auntie.

32:56.880 --> 32:58.640
She's my harshest critic.

32:58.920 --> 33:00.400
I have to be perfect.

33:01.840 --> 33:03.920
She's not half-blind,
she's half-deaf.

33:05.160 --> 33:07.080
So what time will you be back?

33:07.400 --> 33:08.520
Before midnight.

33:10.240 --> 33:11.680
I'll be awake.

34:07.920 --> 34:09.240
Is this your house?

34:09.320 --> 34:10.480
Yes.

34:11.040 --> 34:12.480
Have a seat.

34:23.520 --> 34:25.120
Do I not get a drink?

34:25.840 --> 34:27.040
Please.

34:31.040 --> 34:33.120
-You want one?
-Yes.

34:33.440 --> 34:34.520
Still whisky?

34:36.000 --> 34:37.120
Yes.

34:38.080 --> 34:39.800
But other things have changed.

34:39.880 --> 34:41.600
I saw vans with your name on
at the docks.

34:41.680 --> 34:43.200
Yes, some things have changed.

35:01.440 --> 35:03.120
Tommy, I really wasn't sure
about coming tonight.

35:03.200 --> 35:05.240
I lit a fire in the bedroom upstairs.

35:06.800 --> 35:08.320
(SIGHS) My plan was

35:08.400 --> 35:10.120
that we'd sit here for a while,

35:11.800 --> 35:13.480
talk about old times,

35:13.560 --> 35:14.920
drink some whisky.

35:18.080 --> 35:19.960
And I was gonna tell you

35:20.480 --> 35:21.600
I hadn't spent a day

35:21.680 --> 35:22.960
without thinking about you.

35:23.960 --> 35:25.520
And then we were gonna go upstairs

35:25.600 --> 35:27.040
and sleep together.

35:28.840 --> 35:31.680
But just now on the way
to opening the door,

35:32.200 --> 35:33.520
I changed me mind.

35:36.920 --> 35:38.560
So just have one drink

35:38.640 --> 35:40.120
tell me how happy you are in New York

35:40.200 --> 35:41.600
and then you can go.

35:41.680 --> 35:43.520
-You changed your mind?
-Mmm.

35:44.640 --> 35:45.720
So you can go.

35:46.800 --> 35:48.120
Well...

35:50.400 --> 35:51.400
As a matter of fact,

35:51.480 --> 35:52.840
I am happy in New York.

35:53.640 --> 35:54.800
And I am married.

35:54.880 --> 35:56.600
Oh, yeah, he's... He's rich. I know.

35:56.680 --> 35:57.960
And he's sweet.

35:58.400 --> 36:00.080
And he's kind to me.

36:00.640 --> 36:02.680
So what makes you think that
I would have gone to bed with you

36:02.760 --> 36:05.360
after one whisky and some conversation?

36:05.440 --> 36:07.120
I was accounting for three whiskys.

36:07.200 --> 36:08.560
How dare you?

36:09.080 --> 36:10.880
It doesn't matter now,
'cause I've changed me mind.

36:10.960 --> 36:13.200
I came here because you asked me.

36:13.720 --> 36:15.440
Even though he's sweet
and he's kind to you?

36:15.520 --> 36:16.960
And now I feel like an idiot.

36:17.040 --> 36:18.360
Well, then, go.

36:18.440 --> 36:19.640
Jesus.

36:20.160 --> 36:21.160
(SIGHS)

36:31.240 --> 36:32.920
Well, you're still here.

36:37.240 --> 36:38.240
Are you so certain?

36:38.880 --> 36:40.680
That you're still in love with me?

36:42.400 --> 36:43.680
I was.

36:44.880 --> 36:46.000
But I'm not any more.

36:50.280 --> 36:51.880
You're not armed, Grace, are you?

36:52.280 --> 36:53.800
No, I'm not armed.

36:55.320 --> 36:58.320
I don't carry guns.
I don't have to.

37:04.480 --> 37:06.680
You don't have a sense of humour
any more, either.

37:06.800 --> 37:08.440
What are you talking about?

37:18.440 --> 37:21.680
The thing is, I hate reunions.

37:22.520 --> 37:24.600
I didn't want to sit here
for hours talking about nothing

37:24.680 --> 37:27.480
and dancing around
what we really want to say.

37:28.480 --> 37:29.840
So now,

37:30.920 --> 37:32.080
I know you're happy in New York.

37:32.160 --> 37:34.320
I know your husband's rich
and sweet and kind to you.

37:34.400 --> 37:36.400
I know you're unarmed.

37:37.040 --> 37:40.440
And you didn't come here for sex
because you don't love me any more.

37:41.960 --> 37:43.720
And it's only three minutes past.

37:45.960 --> 37:47.360
Another drink?

37:50.880 --> 37:52.480
I'll take that as a yes.

37:55.280 --> 37:57.760
(SIGHS) It's good to see you, Grace.

38:00.000 --> 38:01.880
So you didn't light the fire?

38:06.160 --> 38:07.920
You see, my real plan

38:10.280 --> 38:11.880
was that we go out.

38:13.680 --> 38:15.160
I want to impress you.

38:16.120 --> 38:17.360
Now,

38:19.040 --> 38:20.800
do you like Charlie Chaplin?

38:23.640 --> 38:24.960
Yes, I like Charlie Chaplin.

38:25.440 --> 38:26.520
Good.

38:27.760 --> 38:30.040
I bet you've never heard
Charlie Chaplin speak.

38:32.920 --> 38:34.560
I thought you were taking me
to see Charlie Chaplin.

38:34.640 --> 38:35.680
I am.

38:35.760 --> 38:38.640
-This isn't a picture house.
-No, it's not a picture house.

38:38.720 --> 38:41.760
(CHUCKLES) So how will
I see Charlie Chaplin?

38:41.880 --> 38:44.840
You will see him and you will hear him,
just like I promised.

38:46.040 --> 38:47.720
There you go. There's Chaplin.

38:47.800 --> 38:49.400
-Oh, my God. That's him.
-Mmm-hmm.

38:49.480 --> 38:51.000
That's really Charlie Chaplin in person.

38:51.080 --> 38:54.120
Yep. He's in England
promoting his film.

38:54.200 --> 38:55.680
And how the hell
do you know Charlie Chaplin?

38:55.760 --> 38:58.560
I don't.
I know his bodyguard, Wag McDonald.

38:59.240 --> 39:00.840
It's that chap there.

39:01.040 --> 39:03.720
Wag was a bookie in Birmingham,
then he went to Los Angeles.

39:04.240 --> 39:06.360
You see, Wag is also Romani gypsy,

39:06.440 --> 39:08.640
as is Chaplin, but he keeps it a secret.

39:09.400 --> 39:12.480
Chaplin was born on the Black Patch,
a gypsy camp in Birmingham.

39:13.200 --> 39:16.360
That's why he gave Wag the job,
even though Wag was on the run.

39:16.440 --> 39:17.720
Thank you.

39:19.920 --> 39:22.440
Thank you.
See, we all have our secrets, Grace.

39:23.440 --> 39:25.520
Come on. I'll introduce you.

39:28.760 --> 39:31.920
Hello, Wag.
Mr Chaplin, this is Grace.

39:32.560 --> 39:34.560
GRACE: Hello, Mr Chaplin.

39:37.960 --> 39:39.280
(PHONE RINGING)

39:42.240 --> 39:44.560
-Hello.
-TOMMY: <i>Hello, Mr Campbell.</i>

39:44.760 --> 39:48.160
<i>Uh, you said you knew
my sister's address in Primrose Hill,</i>

39:48.560 --> 39:50.680
<i>so I expect you have men
watching the house,</i>

39:50.760 --> 39:52.360
<i>see who comes and goes.</i>

39:53.320 --> 39:55.800
Well, tonight your men
will see me return to the house

39:55.880 --> 39:57.480
with a very beautiful woman.

39:58.040 --> 40:00.640
She will stay
until just before midnight.

40:01.080 --> 40:03.280
Of course, I'll close the curtains.

40:04.760 --> 40:06.040
Can you guess who the woman is?

40:09.440 --> 40:10.480
Liar!

40:10.600 --> 40:12.280
Sleep well, Mr Campbell.

40:15.640 --> 40:17.000
(BREATHING HEAVILY)

40:22.320 --> 40:23.800
(WHISPERING) Tommy.

40:25.480 --> 40:27.200
Tommy, do you have someone?

40:35.440 --> 40:37.120
It's too late, Tommy.

40:38.160 --> 40:39.680
It's 11 :00, Grace.

40:39.760 --> 40:41.440
I mean, it's too late.

40:44.760 --> 40:46.560
If you'd come with me to New York...

40:47.480 --> 40:49.160
I have things to do.

40:51.600 --> 40:53.960
You mean the coin landed the wrong way?

40:55.480 --> 40:57.280
It couldn't have worked.

40:58.920 --> 41:00.520
That was a question.

41:11.720 --> 41:12.880
Hey.

41:13.320 --> 41:15.400
Tommy, do you have someone?

41:18.760 --> 41:20.400
I have a racehorse.

41:21.680 --> 41:23.920
She's gonna win the derby.

42:18.080 --> 42:20.280
I'll drive you.
(CLEARS THROAT)

42:25.000 --> 42:26.520
When do you sail back?

42:29.280 --> 42:30.680
We don't know yet.

42:32.280 --> 42:34.000
You don't have a return ticket?

42:35.280 --> 42:37.040
This wasn't right, Tommy.

42:38.560 --> 42:40.400
When do you go back, Grace?

42:45.680 --> 42:47.360
They're doing tests on us.

42:47.720 --> 42:49.680
I don't know when they'll be finished.

42:54.280 --> 42:55.840
We're having treatment.

42:56.960 --> 42:58.680
A doctor on Harley Street.

42:59.720 --> 43:01.560
Some new thing, a breakthrough.

43:05.080 --> 43:06.800
We're trying for a baby.

43:31.480 --> 43:33.560
Why did you come here tonight?

43:39.960 --> 43:42.640
The doctor believes
it's surely me who's at fault.

43:45.560 --> 43:46.720
I'm sorry.

43:47.640 --> 43:49.280
(SIGHS DEEPLY)

43:50.560 --> 43:51.640
It's no one's fault.

43:51.720 --> 43:53.840
I'm tired of that, Tommy.

44:05.400 --> 44:06.840
Can I see you again?

44:11.320 --> 44:12.560
(SOFTLY) Grace.

44:17.800 --> 44:20.080
You're used to working undercover, eh?

44:22.360 --> 44:24.440
I've never lied to him once.

44:27.360 --> 44:29.040
So tell him the truth.

44:48.360 --> 44:49.720
Put your arms up.

44:58.040 --> 45:00.160
Oh, what've we got here then?

45:00.560 --> 45:01.840
(GATE OPENING)

45:04.960 --> 45:06.320
Get your fuckin' hands off me.

45:08.440 --> 45:09.760
Oh, here he is.

45:10.000 --> 45:11.840
The King of London Town.

45:21.760 --> 45:23.040
You been enjoying yourself?

45:23.120 --> 45:24.560
Oh, yeah, it's fucking great.

45:25.560 --> 45:27.720
Surrounded by Sabini's men.

45:28.000 --> 45:29.440
Rats everywhere.

45:30.280 --> 45:31.840
Fucking cockneys.

45:33.000 --> 45:35.160
Well, at least you're going
to get what you've always wanted.

45:35.760 --> 45:36.760
And what's that?

45:36.840 --> 45:39.000
Well, you tried to hang yourself twice.

45:39.080 --> 45:40.680
Now the King is gonna do it for you.

45:41.360 --> 45:42.560
(SCOFFS)

45:45.040 --> 45:47.240
-I've been a fuckin' idiot.
-Yeah.

45:49.200 --> 45:50.920
I haven't appreciated nothing, John.

45:51.000 --> 45:52.480
Are you fucking repenting or something?

45:52.560 --> 45:53.920
Drawing.

45:54.760 --> 45:55.840
I used to be good at drawing.

45:55.920 --> 45:58.480
Arthur, please, for God's sake,
I don't need this.

45:58.560 --> 46:00.280
I should have listened more in class.

46:00.360 --> 46:02.800
What fucking class?
You were never there.

46:04.120 --> 46:05.960
I used to draw horses.

46:06.480 --> 46:08.480
-Arthur...
-Stallions.

46:08.760 --> 46:10.400
-Great big ones.
-Arthur.

46:10.520 --> 46:12.960
-They looked real.
-Not stallions. Not now.

46:13.720 --> 46:16.320
I should have done more
with me life, John.

46:16.760 --> 46:18.640
-Good things.
-Arthur, for God's sake...

46:18.720 --> 46:19.960
Even Ada said it wasn't my fault.

46:20.040 --> 46:21.360
Arthur, will you listen?

46:21.440 --> 46:24.240
-They're gonna hang me, John.
-They're not gonna hang you.

46:24.320 --> 46:25.640
Says who?

46:27.480 --> 46:28.920
Tommy.

46:32.400 --> 46:35.000
And how is Houdini
gonna get me out of this?

46:35.240 --> 46:37.960
-Well, we...
-Don't tell me. He's got a plan.

46:38.800 --> 46:40.600
But you don't know
what that plan is, do you, John?

46:40.680 --> 46:41.760
I do...

46:41.840 --> 46:43.560
'Cause we just can't be trusted.

46:44.200 --> 46:45.400
All right.

46:45.640 --> 46:48.360
If he's so fucking clever,
why am I in here?

46:48.440 --> 46:49.560
Well, it's...

46:49.640 --> 46:52.440
Why is all our men
and half our whisky been lifted?

46:52.840 --> 46:53.960
Hmm?

46:54.200 --> 46:56.160
The Jew and the cockney
have run rings round him.

46:56.240 --> 46:57.960
-Will you shut up?
-Look at you. Look.

46:58.960 --> 47:02.080
-A big fucking man...
-Fucking shut up!

47:04.680 --> 47:06.760
He's already told me
what I've got to do.

47:24.600 --> 47:26.680
What business have you got here?

47:26.840 --> 47:28.200
I just pulled over.

47:28.280 --> 47:30.680
I never smoke and drive, you know?

47:30.760 --> 47:32.840
-Where are you from?
-I'm from Ireland,

47:33.600 --> 47:35.800
the beautiful north
where the rocks sing in the wind.

47:35.880 --> 47:37.480
Yeah, in the beautiful north.

47:38.000 --> 47:39.280
You know,
I've just pulled over for a fag.

47:39.360 --> 47:41.160
I want to see some identification!

47:41.680 --> 47:42.840
Hey!

48:23.320 --> 48:24.400
Look.

48:24.960 --> 48:26.000
Come!

48:29.680 --> 48:30.720
See?

48:31.840 --> 48:33.120
(TOMMY CHUCKLES)

48:35.000 --> 48:38.040
Does it really stop the horses
from getting worms?

48:38.480 --> 48:40.400
Yep. It really does.

48:46.040 --> 48:48.360
Anyway, I thought
it would make you smile.

48:50.360 --> 48:51.800
I'm sorry that you had
to drive through the night.

48:51.880 --> 48:54.640
You must be exhausted.
You can go and sleep if you want.

48:56.760 --> 48:57.920
May.

48:59.920 --> 49:01.560
We have to stop.

49:02.200 --> 49:03.360
This.

49:04.800 --> 49:07.160
I came here
to tell you we have to stop.

49:09.720 --> 49:10.720
Why?

49:11.840 --> 49:14.000
Because I'm me and you're you,
that old thing?

49:15.200 --> 49:16.400
There's someone.

49:19.720 --> 49:21.200
For a long time.

49:26.240 --> 49:28.040
And I didn't want you to think
anything about how

49:28.120 --> 49:30.200
it's gonna be after the race.

49:32.040 --> 49:33.360
(CLEARS THROAT)

49:35.360 --> 49:36.800
Not many of your people know about me,

49:36.880 --> 49:39.600
so I haven't done
the damage that would come.

49:39.720 --> 49:40.920
"My people?"

49:43.840 --> 49:45.640
Well, the damage isn't done,

49:45.800 --> 49:47.200
is what I mean.

49:47.280 --> 49:48.720
-Right.
-It's...

49:51.200 --> 49:54.040
Even if it's like this,
I want the horse to stay here.

49:54.400 --> 49:56.080
To stay? Yes, of course.

49:56.160 --> 49:57.360
Epsom is close.

49:57.440 --> 49:59.800
I haven't got my outfit yet
so it's all right.

50:01.040 --> 50:03.080
You can still be
with me at the enclosure.

50:03.160 --> 50:04.680
That's very gracious of you, sir.

50:05.600 --> 50:06.680
You can wear something.

50:06.800 --> 50:07.800
It's funny, isn't it?

50:07.880 --> 50:10.640
Because you'll be up there
and I'll be down in the ring.

50:11.720 --> 50:13.440
Sort of upside down, isn't it?

50:14.480 --> 50:17.240
You can still be with me after
and you can still wear something.

50:17.320 --> 50:19.200
I'll be covered in mud from the ring.

50:22.360 --> 50:24.320
May, forget about men like me.

50:24.400 --> 50:26.160
I was going to tell you
how much he's improved.

50:32.200 --> 50:33.440
There are other men, May.

50:33.520 --> 50:36.400
I think she stands
a chance of placing, so...

50:36.600 --> 50:37.760
That's the silly part
of our business done.

50:37.840 --> 50:39.920
Are you going to drive
straight off to Birmingham? Or...

50:46.040 --> 50:48.160
And what if I said, uh,

50:48.360 --> 50:51.320
"All right, I'll stay,"
after what I just said?

50:57.760 --> 50:59.600
Then that would be all right.

51:05.200 --> 51:07.000
You talk about damage.

51:07.280 --> 51:08.400
The damage not yet done.

51:08.480 --> 51:09.720
You don't think that half
of London already thinks

51:09.800 --> 51:11.120
that I'm fucking a racketeer?

51:12.600 --> 51:15.480
Laughing about it. Laying on bets
about when you'll steal the silver.

51:18.360 --> 51:20.920
You think your people are ruthless?
Try mine.

51:24.960 --> 51:27.200
So that's why you carry on, eh?

51:27.800 --> 51:29.720
Because you can't back down.

51:30.000 --> 51:31.400
(MAY SCOFFS)

51:31.480 --> 51:34.360
Amongst many other illogical reasons.

51:38.600 --> 51:40.400
So will you drive straight off or...

51:40.480 --> 51:43.120
I haven't got any petrol in the garage.

51:46.920 --> 51:49.040
Yeah. I have some cans
of petrol in the car.

51:49.120 --> 51:50.840
Good. So you can go.

51:58.880 --> 52:00.160
(TOMMY CLEARS THROAT)

52:20.040 --> 52:21.520
They look happy in there, eh?

52:23.720 --> 52:24.960
And why wouldn't they be?

52:38.440 --> 52:39.800
Who is she?

52:41.960 --> 52:44.000
Someone who's sailing away.

52:48.440 --> 52:49.680
(SIGHS)

52:53.240 --> 52:54.640
So let her sail.

52:58.400 --> 52:59.760
You've told me about her
like a gentleman.

52:59.840 --> 53:01.760
Now kindly behave like a gangster again.

53:07.040 --> 53:09.200
Feel sorry for me. It's fine.

53:19.760 --> 53:21.920
Because your horse
will come fifth or sixth.

53:23.880 --> 53:25.520
But I will win you.

53:33.680 --> 53:37.680
Mr Shelby's just parking his car.
He said for you to wait in here.

53:42.560 --> 53:44.400
Isn't this impressive?

53:45.400 --> 53:48.160
And what is it you exactly do here?

53:49.640 --> 53:52.840
I exactly am a secretary to Mr Shelby.

53:52.920 --> 53:55.200
A secretary? My, my, my.

53:56.560 --> 53:58.080
All that paperwork.

54:00.560 --> 54:01.840
Do you want tea?

54:02.520 --> 54:03.520
No.

54:41.880 --> 54:43.200
(DOOR SLAMS SHUT)

54:49.400 --> 54:51.800
I keep everything locked up,
Mr Campbell.

54:51.920 --> 54:53.440
Everything of value.

54:54.240 --> 54:56.120
(TOMMY CLEARS THROAT)

55:01.840 --> 55:03.520
Take a seat.

55:08.120 --> 55:10.760
How is your company treasurer, Polly?

55:13.040 --> 55:17.040
-Why do you ask?
-Oh, just give her my regards.

55:20.640 --> 55:21.640
(EXHALES)

55:27.760 --> 55:30.440
You like to play with fire,

55:30.920 --> 55:32.440
don't you, Mr Shelby?

55:34.120 --> 55:36.880
Yesterday in Belgravia,

55:37.920 --> 55:40.880
Field Marshal Russell's
house was burnt out.

55:40.960 --> 55:43.520
An incendiary device was
put through his letterbox,

55:43.600 --> 55:44.880
which means

55:46.240 --> 55:48.800
that he will have to find
somewhere else to live

55:49.080 --> 55:50.760
for at least the next three months.

55:51.280 --> 55:52.480
Hmm.

55:53.200 --> 55:55.800
Which also means that your plan,

55:55.880 --> 55:57.800
for me to break in
and shoot him in his bed,

55:57.880 --> 56:00.120
is now no longer
an operational possibility.

56:00.200 --> 56:01.480
Indeed.

56:01.760 --> 56:05.720
But if you think a wee burn
frees you from your obligations,

56:05.800 --> 56:08.840
-think again.
-I will keep my side of the bargain.

56:09.080 --> 56:10.120
Oh, by God, you will.

56:10.200 --> 56:11.640
I will shoot your field marshal,

56:11.720 --> 56:14.320
but I will do it in a way
that serves my purpose.

56:14.400 --> 56:16.320
The only purpose is my purpose.

56:16.400 --> 56:19.440
I will carry out your assassination
at a place of my choosing.

56:21.680 --> 56:23.080
Listen to me.

56:23.880 --> 56:27.000
All operational detail
must be mutually agreed.

56:27.080 --> 56:29.800
I'm a soldier. I've experience.
I will determine where and when he...

56:29.880 --> 56:33.280
Now that man has 24-hour
armed police protection...

56:33.360 --> 56:35.120
Your plan was full of holes.

56:35.200 --> 56:36.800
My plan was mutually agreed!

56:36.880 --> 56:38.760
Well, now your plan is up in smoke.

56:39.280 --> 56:41.880
And I have formulated
the only viable alternative.

56:42.400 --> 56:44.160
Oh, for God's sake, what do you mean?

56:45.680 --> 56:47.440
How would you get to him?

56:49.840 --> 56:52.200
I won't.
He will come to me.

56:53.880 --> 56:54.880
(SCOFFS)

56:56.800 --> 56:58.720
Now, listen to me, Mr Shelby.

56:59.080 --> 57:00.960
When this meeting is concluded,

57:01.120 --> 57:04.440
I must report directly
to Mr Winston Churchill.

57:05.120 --> 57:08.520
Your relationship with Mr Churchill
is not my concern.

57:09.520 --> 57:13.520
And Mr Winston Churchill
will need to hear detail.

57:14.000 --> 57:16.200
Well, you tell him
he'll have to trust me.

57:20.480 --> 57:22.760
Look, Mr Campbell.
(CLEARS THROAT)

57:23.160 --> 57:25.320
I will carry out my mission.

57:25.840 --> 57:27.000
-Good.
-Good.

57:28.200 --> 57:30.600
But I will do it in a place
where it will be impossible

57:30.680 --> 57:34.800
for you or your men
to have me shot afterwards.

57:36.880 --> 57:38.480
Because that was the plan.

57:39.160 --> 57:40.160
Eh?

57:40.520 --> 57:42.720
Coppers front and back. No way out.

57:42.920 --> 57:44.960
Me shot dead, dumped in the Thames.

57:45.440 --> 57:46.880
I will do the killing,

57:47.360 --> 57:49.600
but at a place
where that will not be an option.

57:52.120 --> 57:55.760
I've recently become
a racehorse owner, Mr Campbell.

58:00.520 --> 58:01.800
It's, uh...

58:03.680 --> 58:06.040
Well, perhaps you can guess
which one is my horse.

58:06.240 --> 58:07.480
(COUGHS)

58:24.360 --> 58:26.160
Where and when?

58:28.680 --> 58:29.800
Epsom.

58:30.920 --> 58:32.000
Derby Day.

58:32.024 --> 58:37.024
http://hiqve.com/
